description: From Latin exauguratus, past participle of exaugurare (“to profane”), from ex (“out”) + augurari (“to act as an augur”), from augur.

verbs.description: exaugurate (third-person singular simple present exaugurates, present participle exaugurating, simple past and past participle exaugurated)

entries.meaning: (obsolete, transitive) To annul the consecration of; to secularize or unhallow.
